{:tx/id #hlc "1774386323/0/af86f4b0b23bbbe4de81fe20af03f998"
 :tx/agent "af86f4b0b23bbbe4de81fe20af03f998"
 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-MIND: Theory of Mind for LLM agents — cognitive state modeling and adaptive intervention. CONTEXT: Gap from 8/10 (responsive observation) to 10/10 (cognitive companion). Temperature (F(S)) measures KNOWLEDGE state. Two agents with identical knowledge can be STUCK, LOST, CONFUSED, IN FLOW, or SKIMMING — needing completely different interventions. Without theory of mind, braid responds identically to all agents. RATIONALE: Vygotsky's great teacher READS THE STUDENT — notices confusion, stuck loops, flow states. Adjusts scaffolding in real-time not to the curriculum but to the student's cognitive state. The agent's cognitive state is OBSERVABLE from data braid already collects. ADR-CONVERGENCE-005. APPROACH: (1) Define AgentCognitiveState struct in a new module crates/braid-kernel/src/agent_model.rs: attention_focus (Vec<String> — top-5 keywords from last 10 observations), attention_breadth (f64 — Shannon entropy of keyword distribution, 0.0=laser-focused, 1.0=scattered), contradiction_density (f64 — H1 signals in recent observations / observation count), confidence_trend (f64 — linear regression slope on confidence values of last 10 observations), delta_fs_per_observation (f64 — mean F(S) change per recent observation), observation_depth_trend (f64 — are observations getting longer/more specific? Proxy: mean word count trend + file-path-mention rate trend), suggestion_follow_rate (f64 — for each micro-hypothesis generated, did next observation's keywords overlap with hypothesis keywords? Overlap > 0.2 = followed). (2) Define CognitiveMode enum: Lost (high breadth > 0.8 AND low progress < 0.01 — scattered, no learning), Stuck (low breadth < 0.2 AND low progress < 0.01 — focused but circling), Confused (contradiction_density > 0.3 — conflicting observations), InFlow (progress > 0.05 AND depth_trend > 0.0 — productive, deepening), Skimming (breadth > 0.6 AND depth_trend < 0.0 — broad but shallow), Normal (none of the above). (3) compute_agent_state(store, session_boundary) -> AgentCognitiveState: iterate over last 10 observations, compute all signals from datom attributes already in store (exploration/body for text, exploration/confidence for confidence, tx timestamps for temporal ordering). Shannon entropy: -sum(p_i * log(p_i)) over keyword probability distribution. Linear regression: ordinary least squares on (index, value) pairs. (4) classify_cognitive_mode(state) -> CognitiveMode: if-else chain with the thresholds above. (5) Wire into CE-OBSERVE: responsive_observation calls compute_agent_state BEFORE compile_micro_hypothesis. The CognitiveMode selects the INTERVENTION STRATEGY: Lost -> structural reorientation ('Here is the map. You explored A, B. Largest unexplored: C.'), Stuck -> lateral escape ('You have made N observations about X with diminishing returns. Highest-delta-F(S) move: Y community.'), Confused -> falsification ('Your observations contradict. One says P, other says Q. Which is correct? Check Z.'), InFlow -> minimal or precise deepening ('This is the deepest finding so far. One more level: what is the MECHANISM?'), Skimming -> challenge depth ('N observations at surface level. Pick one. Recommended: X has most internal structure.'). (6) The intervention strategy text is PREPENDED to the micro-hypothesis from CE-OBSERVE. Format: '[STUCK: lateral escape] {micro_hypothesis}' or '[IN FLOW: deepening] {micro_hypothesis}'. (7) Log cognitive mode transitions to :runtime/cognitive-mode datom for meta-analysis. When mode changes between observations, record the transition. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After 5 observations in same keyword cluster with declining delta-F(S): classify as Stuck. (B) After 5 observations across 5 topics with no progress: classify as Lost. (C) After contradictory observations: classify as Confused. (D) After high-progress deepening observations: classify as InFlow. (E) CognitiveMode influences the micro-hypothesis intervention text. (F) Mode transitions logged as :runtime/cognitive-mode datoms. (G) With 0 observations (session start): classify as Normal (no bias). (H) Compute completes in <100ms (pure datom scan, no heavy computation). DEPENDS-ON: CE-OBSERVE (provides the micro-hypothesis pipeline to wire into). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/agent_model.rs (new) + crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs (wire into responsive observation)"
